20or%20walking%20pattern%20all%20help%20us%20stay%20mobile%20and%20independent%20as%20we%20age%2C%20according%20to%20the%20authors%20based%20at%20Mayo%20Clinic.%20Looking%20at%20how%20these%20factors%20change%20over%20time%2C%20and%20how%20quickly%2C%20can%20help%20clinicians%20develop%20better%20programs%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexercise-for-healthy-aging-longevity-strength-training-personal-trainer-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20aging%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20said%20in%20the%20study%20published%20Wednesday%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0310764%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPLOS%20ONE%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20an%20individual%20level%2C%20measuring%20these%20things%20can%20make%20a%20person%20of%20certain%20weaknesses%2C%20which%20they%20can%20then%20take%20steps%20to%20improve%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20do%20the%20test%20and%20two%20other%20easy%20ways%20to%20determine%20whether%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiological-age-test-calculation-interpret-results-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaging%20healthily%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dbdcbc58-7ed3-4563-8f32-24e4dd3e522f%5C%22%3E1)%20Balance%20test%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20body%20systems%2C%20including%20the%20muscles%2C%20bones%2C%20joints%2C%20eyes%2C%20nerves%2C%20and%20inner%20ear%2C%20help%20us%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20ability%20to%20balance%20declines%20faster%20than%20both%20strength%20and%20gait%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%2C%20and%20once%20it%20does%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20falling%20rises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20poor%20balance%2C%20you're%20at%20risk%20of%20falling%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20you're%20moving.%20Falls%20are%20a%20severe%20health%20risk%20with%20serious%20consequence%2C%26quot%3B%20senior%20author%20Kenton%20Kaufman%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20one%20in%20four%20people%20over%2065%20fall%20each%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Institute%20on%20Aging.%20If%20a%20person%20breaks%20their%20bones%2C%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20other%20serious%20health%20problems%20and%20can%20cause%20long-term%20disability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202022%20study%20published%20in%20the%20British%20Journal%20of%20Sports%20Medicine%20on%201%2C702%20adults%20aged%20between%2051%20and%2075%2C%20being%20unable%20to%20stand%20on%20one%20leg%20for%2010%20seconds%20was%20linked%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20dying%20from%20any%20cause%20within%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%20study's%2040%20participants%2C%20who%20were%20aged%20between%2052%20and%2083%2C%20could%20stand%20on%20their%20nondominant%20leg%20for%2017%20seconds.%20The%20average%20for%20those%20over%2065%20was%2011%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20stand%20on%20one%20leg%20for%2030%20seconds%2C%20you%20are%20doing%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaufman%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20can%20easily%20take%20steps%20to%20train%20their%20balance%2C%20for%20example%2C%20by%20practicing%20standing%20on%20one%20leg.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22333c2dc3-b61b-4531-8bb9-cce59300d24e%5C%22%3E2)%20Five-second%20walking%20test%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20walking%20fast%20on%20a%20bridge.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671b8c4301ea6d83dee407dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHow%20fast%20you%20can%20walk%20in%20a%20short%20time%20can%20indicate%20how%20fit%20you%20are%20for%20your%20age.%20%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20doctors%20at%20longevity%20clinics%20swear%20by%20a%20simple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-experts-use-walking-test-to-measu