sinsider.com%2Fwhy-ukraine-needs-gripen-fighter-jets-long-term-f-16s-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Gripen%20can%20fight%20from%20improvised%20runways%2C%20is%20easier%20to%20maintain%2C%20and%20was%20designed%20with%20the%20Russian%20threat%20in%20mind.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbaker%40insider.com%20(Sin%C3%A9ad%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ukraine-needs-gripen-fighter-jets-long-term-f-16s-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tesla%20earnings%20have%20reinvigorated%20investors%20but%20some%20growth%20drivers%20look%20'unsustainable%2C'%20JPMorgan%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tesla%20has%20a%20lengthy%20hiring%20process.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6699275380d4d5da13d4e875%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETesla%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%3Cp%3EVCG%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETesla%20closed%2022%25%20higher%20on%20Thursday%2C%20its%20best%20day%20in%20years%20after%20posting%20strong%20earnings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnalysts%20at%20JPMorgan%20caution%20that%20some%20of%20the%20automaker's%20growth%20drivers%20aren't%20sustainable.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20of%20the%20factors%20JPMorgan%20questioned%20include%20strong%20sales%20of%20regulatory%20credits%20in%20the%20quarter.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETesla's%20earnings%20beat%20fueled%20a%20huge%20rally%20for%20the%20stock%20on%20Thursday%2C%20but%20JPMorgan%20is%20urging%20caution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20at%20the%20bank%20said%20that%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-stock-tsla-earnings-call-report-live-updates-2024-10%3F_gl%3D1*1b1iqo9*_ga*MTY3OTgyNjg0MS4xNzIxMDE2MDM2*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcyOTc3NDk1OC4zMDguMS4xNzI5Nzc1Nzk4LjYwLjAuMA..%23wedbush-analyst-dan-ives-sticks-with-bullish-view-on-tesla-despite-recent-volatility%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrong%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20boost%20the%20stock%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20the%20automaker's%20growth%20drivers%20might%20not%20be%20sustainable%20in%20the%20coming%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20correctly%20called%20the%20big%20reaction%20in%20the%20stock%20on%20Thursday%20post-earnings%2C%20with%20shares%20rising%2022%25%2C%20but%20they%20added%20that%20they%20see%20some%20caveats%20to%20the%20company's%20outlook.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20we%20at%20the%20same%20time%20see%20several%20potentially%20unsustainable%20drivers%20of%203Q's%20better%20earnings%20and%20cash%20flow%20performance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20pointed%20in%20particular%20to%20Tesla's%20near-record%20sales%20of%20regulatory%20credits.%20Tesla%20can%20sell%20credits%20it%20receives%20for%20producing%20electric%20cars%20to%20other%20companies%20that%20don't%20meet%20government%20emissions%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20hugely%20profitable%20business%2C%20and%20the%20credits%20generated%20%24739%20million%20for%20Tesla%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20quarter%2C%20the%20second-highest%20amount%20after%20the%20previous%20quarter's%20%24890%20million.%20While%20the%20credits%20are%20a%20huge%20profit%20driver%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%20JPMorgan%20analysts%20said%20that%20won't%20last%20as%20other%20automakers%20introduce%20their%20own%20EVs%20and%20buy%20fewer%20credits%20from%20competitors%20like%20Tesla.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestors%20should%20be%20cautious%20about%20capitalizing%20the%20earnings%20generated%20from%20these%20(100%25%20margin)%20credits%2C%20given%20that%20one%20of%20the%20tenets%20of%20the%20Tesla%20bull%20case%20is%20the%20large%20scale%20electrification%20of%20the%20automotive%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAs%20other%20automakers%20broaden%20their%20electric%20offerings%2C%20they%20should%20over%20time%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20generate%20their%20own%20credits%2C%20negating%20and%20eventually%20eliminating%20the%20flow%20of%20competitor%20payments%20to%20Tesla.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20also%20pointed%20to%20large%20working%20capital%20benefits%2C%20which%20they%20say%20are%20unsustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20saw%20a%20large%20beat%20on%20free%20cash%20flow%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20quarter%2C%20but%20that%20was%20in%20part%20due%20to%20a%20large%20increase%20in%20the%20amount%20due%20to%20its%20suppliers%20and%20other%20accrued%20liabilities%2C%20the%20analysts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20has%20only%20ever%20generated%20more%20cash%20from%20an%20increase%20in%20accounts%20payable%20in%20one%20other%20quarter%2C%20but%20at%20that%20time%2C%20deliveries%20and%20production%20both%20grew%20much%20faster%2C%20the%20analysts%20said.%20They%20wrote%20in%20the%20note%20that%20this%20suggests%20that%20this%20driver%20of%20the%20quarter's%20strong%20cash%20flow%20is%20unsustainable%20and%20possibly%20reversing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAutomakers%20are%20expected%20to%20generate%20cash%20from%20working%20capital%20as%20sales%20rise%2C%20given%20timing%20differences%20arising%20from%20the%20favorable%20trade%20terms%20they%20enjoy%20with%20suppliers%2C%20but%20digging%20more%20deeply%20into%20the%20benefit%2C%20we%20note%20only%20in%20one%20quarter%20has%20Tesla%20ever%20generated%20more%20cash%20from%20an%20increase%20in%20accounts%20payable%20than%20it%20did%20in%203Q24%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20automaker%20reported%20earnings%20per%20share%20of%20%240.62%20for%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20outpacing%20analysts'%20expectations%20of%20%240.51.%20Its%20operating%20profit%20came%20in%20at%20%242.7%20billion%2C%20exceeding%20expectations%20of%20%242.0%20billion%20and%20marking%20a%2054%25%20increase%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%20The%20company%20also%20a